14 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Legislative intent. (1) It is the intent of the legislature that [this act] be
15 quickly implemented by the department of commerce and that the department develop and implement a grant
16 application process that is efficient and user-friendly. The application must include:
17 (a) the name, address, telephone number, and e-mail address of the applicant, the name of the
18 contact person, and the contact person's contact information, if different from the applicant;
19 (b) a statement of the problem or problems the applicant is experiencing that the grant is expected
20 to address. Examples include repairing a leaky roof, replacing an obsolete stove, or insufficient insulation in the
21 building.
22 (c) a list of activities the applicant plans to undertake using the grant funds to address the
23 identified problem or problems. Examples include replacing the roof, purchasing a new stove, or adding 18
24 inches of fiber fill insulation to the attic.
25 (d) a cost estimate for each of the proposed activities to be undertaken by the applicant. The
26 estimate must be supported by documents from contractors, equipment vendors, and other parties who plan to
27 provide services to the applicant.
28 (e) a schedule of when the proposed project is to commence and be completed; and
